{{Quote|[[Hydra]] was founded on the belief that humanity could not be trusted with its own freedom. What we did not realize was that if you try to take that freedom, they resist. The [[World War II|war]] taught us much. Humanity needed to surrender its freedom willingly.|Arnim Zola to [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Doctor '''Arnim Zola''' was a Swiss-born scientist working for [[Hydra]] before, during, and after [[World War II]]. Originally an employee of the [[Sturmabteilung]], Zola was recruited in [[1934]] by [[Johann Schmidt]] to become a lead scientist for Hydra. During the early days of World War II, Zola was assigned by Schmidt to study the [[Tesseract]] to build powered advanced weapons, which Schmidt intended to use in his quest for world domination. However, as the war came to an end, [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and the [[Howling Commandos]] tracked down Zola to his [[Schnellzug EB912|train]], eventually succeeding in [[Capture of Arnim Zola|capturing him]].

Despite being captured by the Allies shortly before Schmidt's [[Battle in the Valkyrie|defeat]] in [[1945]], Zola was offered a position in [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], the newly formed peacekeeping organization, as part of [[Operation Paperclip]]. However, Zola actually used his new position to secretly rebuild [[Hydra]] from the shadows. Furthermore, thanks to his machinations during the war, Zola enabled [[Bucky Barnes]] to survive his apparent death while trying to capture him, leading Zola to recover Barnes and experiment on him, mechanically brainwashing Barnes into the Hydra operative, as a part of [[Winter Soldier Program]].

Eventually, Zola received a fatal diagnosis in [[1972]] and passed away, but his mind was transferred into a complex computer system on [[Camp Lehigh]], where he remained from that point onward, aiding his fellow [[Hydra]] allies undetected. In [[2014]], however, when he was discovered by [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and [[Black Widow]] to still be active, Zola stalled them by informing them about Hydra's history and agenda before missiles sent by [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] destroyed Camp Lehigh in an attempt to kill Rogers and Romanoff, causing Zola's demise.

==Biography==
===Nazi Scientist===
====Recruited by Johann Schmidt====
[[File:Zola 1934 1.PNG|{{AltFloat}}|Zola in [[Kummersdorf]]]]
{{Quote|I am working on advanced [[Hydra Exo-Skeleton|exo-skeleton]] technology... To make o-one soldier fight ...like a battalion...|Arnim Zola to [[Johann Schmidt]]|Captain America: First Vengeance}}
Born in [[Switzerland]], Arnim Zola eventually relocated to [[Germany]] and went on to become one of its top scientists. With the rise of the Nazis, Zola found himself working for the Third Reich, helping to build [[Adolf Hitler]]'s war machine. In [[1934]], he worked at [[Sturmabteilung]]'s Weapons Testing Grounds at [[Kummersdorf]]. Among his inventions was the advanced [[Hydra Exo-Skeleton|exo-skeleton]], which could virtually turn a soldier into a one-man battalion. In July, Kummersdorf was attacked by the [[Schutzstaffel]] troops led by [[Johann Schmidt]] who killed almost the entire personnel of the base. Zola was spared only because he agreed to carry out genetics research for Schmidt, who wanted to use Zola's knowledge to turn himself into a superior man.{{Ref|CAFV2}}

====Working for Hydra====
Soon, [[Johann Schmidt]] organized his own SS division, [[Hydra]]. Zola became Hydra's top scientist. In [[1935|September 1935]], Zola was allowed to resume his work on exoskeleton battle suits and various high-tech weaponry because Schmidt captured [[Abraham Erskine]] who worked on the [[Super Soldier Serum]]. By the time of the {{WPS|Spanish Civil War}}, Zola had created several advanced war machines. His finished exo-skeleton battle suit was used by Hydra against the {{WPS|Republican faction (Spanish Civil War)|Spanish Republicans}} at [[Guernica]] in [[1937]]. Zola also worked on paranormal and occult sciences.{{Ref|CAFV2}}

===[[World War II]]===
====Schmidt's Transformation====
{{Quote|How does it feel, Abraham? To have your hubris be responsible for the deaths of your [[Greta Erskine|wife]] and [[Klaus Erskine|chil]][[Marlene Erskine|dren]]?|Arnim Zola to [[Abraham Erskine]]|Captain America: First Vengeance}}
In [[1940|November 1940]], Zola was at [[Castle Kaufmann]] when [[Johann Schmidt]] tested the unstable [[Super Soldier Serum]] on himself. The serum enhanced his strength, but it also disfigured his face. Two days later, Zola visited [[Abraham Erskine]] in his cell and told him that Schmidt will kill him for failing to give him what he wanted. However, Zola and all guards in the castle were drugged by [[Peggy Carter]] who helped Erskine to escape.{{Ref|CAFV3}}

====Studying the Tesseract====
[[File:Arnim Zola Comic Easter Egg.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola studies the [[Tesseract]]]]
{{Quote|The energy we have just collected could power my designs. All my designs. This will change the [[World War II|war]]."<br>"Doctor Zola, this will change the world.|Arnim Zola and [[Johann Schmidt]]|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
When [[Hydra]] forces found the [[Tesseract]] in [[1942]], Zola was ordered by [[Johann Schmidt]] to study and recreate its power. While Schmidt remained eager to begin the experiments to help his army defeat the Allies and win the war, Zola was more skeptical and insisted that they take their time as he was unsure if his machines would even work.
[[File:Captain-america-disneyscreencaps com-2133.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola captures the [[Tesseract]]'s energy]]
Eventually, Schmidt forced Zola to begin the experiment and despite Zola's warnings, Schmidt pushed for an incautious approach to test the device's power. As a result, Zola accidentally discovered how to transform its energy into advanced laser ammunition and engines to be used against the [[United States Armed Forces]]. Zola designed advanced weapons for Hydra, with his suits, [[Arnimhilation 99L Assault Weapon|weapons]], [[Landkreuzer|vehicles]], and [[Tesseract Cradle|equipment]] helping Hydra became more powerful than ever.
[[File:Captain-america-disneyscreencaps com-3087.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola learns [[Abraham Erskine]] has been found]]
Later, Zola arrived in [[Johann Schmidt]]'s office to find him having his portrait painted, using his true red face, while [[Richard Wagner]]'s ''Götterdämmerung'' played from the gramophone. Schmidt informed Zola that [[Hydra]] had finally discovered [[Abraham Erskine]]'s location. As Zola asked if he should give the order for Erskine's assassination, Schmidt responded that the order was already given before asking Zola's opinion on the painting, which Zola called a masterpiece.{{Ref|CATFA}}

====Departing from the Reich====
[[File:Doctor Arnim Zola.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola watches [[Johann Schmidt]] kill [[Adolf Hitler|Hitler]]'s men]]
{{Quote|As you can see, production of the ''[[Valkyrie (Vehicle)|Valkyrie]]'' is progressing on schedule, even with components of this size.|Arnim Zola|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
When three SS officers came to [[Johann Schmidt]]'s [[Hydra Headquarters|base]] to question him about the progress in developing advanced weapons for [[Germany|Third Reich]], Schmidt showed them [[Tesseract]] powered weapons made by Zola. But when they discovered that Schmidt intended to nuke [[Berlin]], Schmidt vaporized them with his [[Hydra Cannon|advanced cannon]]. Schmidt told Zola that Hydra could grow no further in [[Adolf Hitler]]'s shadow, to which Zola responded by saying "Hail Hydra", despite his horror at the sudden violence against their former allies.
[[File:Arnim-Zola-questions-RedSkull-CATFA.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola and [[Johann Schmidt]] explore their facility]]
With Hydra self-funded, Zola and Schmidt explored the [[Hydra Base Camp C3]] where prisoners of war were being forced to build weapons powered by the Tesseract. Schmidt ordered that they increase their workload by an exceptional amount; when Zola warned that such an increased workload would very likely kill the men, Schmidt was not concerned, noting that they could always get more workers. Once Schmidt left, Zola contemplated this.{{Ref|CATFA}}

====Captain America's Raid====
[[File:Schmidt Setting Destruction.png|{{AltFloat}}|Zola witnesses [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]'s attack]]
{{Quote|No, no, no, what are you doing?"<br>"[[Hydra|Our forces]] are outmatched.|Arnim Zola and [[Johann Schmidt]]|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
In [[1943|November 1943]], [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] arrived at the [[Hydra Base Camp C3|Hydra base]] in [[Austria]] to [[Liberation of Allied Prisoners of War|rescue the Allied soldiers]] they were using as menial labor there. When [[Johann Schmidt]] saw this he immediately hit the self-destruct on the base, despite Zola's protests. Zola watched on a monitor as Captain America defeated their guards with ease.
[[File:Arnim-Zola-escaping.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola collects his papers while escaping]]
With only minutes to spare, Zola ran to his lab where [[Bucky Barnes]] was being experimented on; he grabbed his documents for his many designs, including a battle suit. With everything he needed, Zola went back out to the corridor where he was spotted by Captain America. Zola made a run for it and, fortunately for him, the Captain let him go when he became distracted by rescuing Barnes, his friend, from the table where Zola's experiments had taken place.
[[File:Arnim-Zola-Exploding-HYDRA-Base-CATFA.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola and Schmidt challenge [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]]]
Before long the base's self-destruct had activated and much of the equipment exploded. As Zola and Schmidt made their escape from the base, they encountered Captain America and Barnes who was also looking for an escape. Both the Captain and Schmidt engaged in a battle where they showed themselves to be equally matched in strength, but Zola quickly separated them by pulling the bridge back. Schmidt then pulled off [[Johann Schmidt's Prosthetic Mask|his mask]] and revealed his true face.
[[File:Captain-america-disneyscreencaps com-7492.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola and [[Red Skull]] make their escape]]
Schmidt and Zola then left the pair to die in the explosions. While the base exploded and began burning to the ground, Schmidt prepared to take off in a [[Focke-Wulf Triebflügel|single man rocket]]; upon seeing this Zola questioned how he would escape, Schmidt relented and gave Zola the keys to [[Johann Schmidt's Coupe|his coupe]], mercifully allowing his top scientist to escape the self-destructing factory, but not before warning him not to scratch the car at all under the threat of death.
[[File:Captain-america-disneyscreencaps com-7549.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola escapes the exploding Hydra base]]
Schmidt then left on the rocket to regroup with Zola at another time in their [[Hydra Headquarters]] while Zola made it to the car and, with a smile on his face due to driving such an impressive vehicle, made his escape as the facility was destroyed; however, Rogers and Barnes also escaped and rejoined the [[United States Army]], using the information stolen from Zola's lab to begin gaining an advantage in their war against the [[Red Skull]] and Hydra's plans for world domination.{{Ref|CATFA}}

====Losing the War====
[[File:Arnim Zola.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola overlooks yet another destroyed base]]
{{Quote|This is hardly my area of expertise! I... I merely develop the weapons. I... I cannot fire them."<br>"Finish your mission, doctor. Before the [[Steve Rogers|American]] finishes his.|Arnim Zola and [[Red Skull]]|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
As [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and his [[Howling Commandos]] were progressively managing to destroy most major [[Hydra]] operations, preventing Zola from completing any real ability to work on his own scientific projects. Zola was then ordered by Red Skull to end the Captain and his allies' assaults on Hydra bases but was unsuccessful. The more Hydra facilities were destroyed, the angrier and more deranged [[Red Skull]] became. Zola witnessed Schmidt threaten his life before murdering his own soldiers with Zola's [[Hydra Pistol]] for failing to defend his facilities.{{Ref|CATFA}}

In [[1944|April 1944]], Zola was in a castle on an island in the Nazi occupied [[Denmark|Danish]] Straits. The castle was invaded by [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]], who managed to destroy one of Zola's [[Hydra Exo-Skeleton|exo-skeleton suits]] and [[Hydra Mini Tank|an armored vehicle]].{{Ref|CAFV4}}

====[[Capture of Arnim Zola|Assault on the Hydra Train]]====
[[File:Arnim-Zola-speaker-train.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola orders his soldiers to kill [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]]]
{{Quote|Stop [[Steve Rogers|him]]! Fire again! Kill him now!|Arnim Zola|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
Eventually, Zola had to be moved via [[Schnellzug EB912|armored train]] to the [[Hydra Headquarters]] to continue his work. Zola soon conceived of a plan to use the train as the setting for a trap for [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] along the {{WPS|Danube|Danube River}}. The train was later [[Capture of Arnim Zola|attacked]] by Captain America, [[Bucky Barnes]] and [[Gabe Jones]] who were attempting to capture Zola under the orders of [[Chester Phillips]]. Having seen his attackers on the video feed, Zola sent in his soldiers and ordered them to kill them, separating Captain America and Barnes and attempting to overpower them in the unexpected ambush.
[[File:Captain-america-disneyscreencaps com-9539.png|{{AltFloat}}|Zola is captured by the [[Howling Commandos]]]]
Captain America and Barnes soon managed to defeat most of their attackers in the ensuing battle, but while they took a moment to catch their breath, Barnes was seemingly killed when he was shot off the side of the train and fell from the mountain, disappearing from sight into a freezing river. Zola's victory over the [[Howling Commandos]] was short-lived, however, when Jones jumped through the ceiling and captured Zola at gunpoint. Zola was then handed over to Allied forces for questioning about Hydra's overall plans.{{Ref|CATFA}}

====In Captivity====
[[File:Arnim Zola Imprisoned.png|{{AltFloat}}|Zola imprisoned by the [[SSR]]]]
{{Quote|[[Red Skull|Schmidt]] believes he walks in the footsteps of the gods. Only the world itself will satisfy him."<br>"You do realize that's nuts, don’t you?"<br>"But the sanity of the plan is of no consequence.|Arnim Zola and [[Chester Phillips]]|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
Zola was quickly taken to the [[Strategic Scientific Reserve]]'s base and interrogated by Colonel [[Chester Phillips]]. Philips went to interrogate him and decided to confuse him by offering him a steak dinner, which was refused; when Zola said it was because he was a vegetarian. Phillips noted that his lack of the [[Cyanide Pills]] normally used by [[Hydra]] agents to prevent capture suggested that he did not want to die personally. Zola told them everything he knew about Hydra and revealed that [[Johann Schmidt]]'s plans were for complete world domination.{{Ref|CATFA}}

===Rebuilding Hydra===
====Meeting Johann Fennhoff====
[[File:Zola-Valediction.png|{{AltFloat}}|Zola introduces himself to [[Johann Fennhoff]]]]
{{Quote|You had a vision, and it didn't come to pass. What is the point of anything now? But given time and a bit of quiet, new visions will arise. I am familiar with your work on matters of the mind, Herr Doktor<ref>Translates from German to: "''Doctor.''"</ref>. It would give me great pleasure to hear your thoughts on this.|Arnim Zola to [[Johann Fennhoff]]|Valediction}}
[[1946|One year after]] the [[World War II|war]], Zola was serving his sentence in a prison in the [[United States of America]]. One day, he was given the [[Leviathan]] scientist [[Johann Fennhoff]] as a cellmate when Fennoff's [[Johann Fennhoff's Revenge Plot|attempts]] to destroy [[Howard Stark]] were stopped by the [[Strategic Scientific Reserve]]. Since Fennhoff's mouth was muzzled so that he could not use his power, Zola requested that he write down exactly how his power worked. Zola was interested in Fennhoff's expertise in the human mind control, knowing that it could be used in [[Hydra]]'s [[Winter Soldier Program|future]] [[Faustus|projects]].{{Ref|AC108}}

====Corrupting S.H.I.E.L.D.====
[[File:Zola After WW2.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola is [[Operation Paperclip|recruited]] by [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]]]
{{Quote|After the [[World War II|war]], [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] was founded, and I was recruited. The new [[Hydra]] grew, a beautiful parasite, inside S.H.I.E.L.D.|Arnim Zola|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
In the aftermath of [[World War II]], the [[United States of America]] started [[Operation Paperclip]], a program used to recruit the scientists of Nazi [[Germany]] for employment by the United States and deny their scientific expertise and knowledge to the [[Soviet Union]].
[[File:Zola's File2.png|{{AltFloat}}|Zola's S.H.I.E.L.D. file]]
As part of the operation, Zola was recruited into [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], the peacekeeping organization taking over from the [[Strategic Scientific Reserve]]. However, the leaders of S.H.I.E.L.D. were unaware that they were, in fact, growing a parasite and using his new position within S.H.I.E.L.D., Zola secretly was able to re-create Hydra completely undetected.
[[File:Zola SHIELD.png|{{AltFloat}}|Zola operates as a [[Hydra]] infiltrator]]
Having learned from Hydra's failures during World War II, Zola and his fellow operatives set out to create a world so chaotic by secretly feeding global crises and reaping wars, in case if history did not cooperate, history was changed in order to ensure that humanity would one day sacrifice its own freedom to ensure its security rather than having to take that freedom away by force.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Creating the Winter Soldier====
[[File:Cap2 5250.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola experiments on [[Bucky Barnes]]]]
{{Quote|Sergeant Barnes... The procedure has already started. You are to be the new fist of [[Hydra]].|Arnim Zola to [[Bucky Barnes]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Using [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s resources, Zola continued his experiments on [[Bucky Barnes]] with other doctors to [[Winter Soldier Program|turn him into Hydra's secret weapon/assassin]]. Zola also managed to build an entire computer system which his mind was uploaded into as an artificially intelligent user interface.{{Ref|CATWS}} By [[1970]], Zola was working in [[Camp Lehigh]], [[New Jersey]] along with [[Hank Pym]] and [[Howard Stark]].{{Ref|AE}}

====Saving his Mind====
{{Quote|In [[1972]], I received a terminal diagnosis. Science could not save my body. My mind, however, that was worth saving on 200,000 feet of databanks.|Arnim Zola to [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
In [[1972]], however, Zola received a terminal diagnosis.{{Ref|CATWS}} He realized that he had not much time left to live, but even with the death of his physical body, Arnim Zola wasn't finished after all: concluding that science couldn't save his body but his mind, Zola had constructed a supercomputer, dubbed as his masterpiece, with the purposes of synthesizing and emulating his own brain through one hundred billion neurons re-created and replicated with microprocessors of his design. In addition, Zola stored his personal journals with date files to ensure that [[Alexander Pierce]] could continue his work after his passing.{{Ref|TWFATEotAaB}}

Zola died shortly afterwards, yet by downloading his consciousness into the computer system he created, his mind continued to live in cyberspace, where he was able to provide easy passage into the agency for [[Hydra]] sleeper agents that either managed to escape justice during the war or were corrupted from within.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Revealing Hydra's Existence====
[[File:Catws 03623.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Arnim Zola displayed on a computer monitor]]
{{Quote|[[Hydra]] created a [[Earth|world]] so chaotic that [[Humans|humanity]] is finally ready to sacrifice its freedom to gain its security. Once the purification process is complete, Hydra's new world order will arise. We won, Captain. Your death amounts to the same as your life. A zero sum.|Arnim Zola to [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
[[2014|Two years after]] the [[Battle of New York]], [[Alexander Pierce]], a senior [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] official who was one of [[Hydra]]'s undercover operatives, attempted to initiate Hydra's new global rule by taking control of [[Project Insight]] under the noses of the [[World Security Council]] and all other S.H.I.E.L.D. agents.
[[File:Computer Zola.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola reveals how [[Hydra]] usurped [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]]]
[[Natasha Romanoff]] and [[Steve Rogers]], in their efforts to stop Pierce following [[Nick Fury]]'s apparent death, discovered a bunker hidden beneath [[Camp Lehigh]] where the mainframe containing Zola's downloaded consciousness was located. At first, when Zola mentioned their names and birthdates, Romanoff thought it was just a recording of Zola's, leading Zola to debunk her theory and that he was indeed the prisoner Rogers captured in [[1945]].
[[File:Catws 03787.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola informs [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] of his [[Zola's Algorithm|algorithm]]]]
Recognizing Zola, Rogers initially couldn't understand why Zola was there as Hydra died when the [[Red Skull]] vanished with the [[Tesseract]], but Zola revealed that while the science couldn't save his physical body from dying, his mind could indeed, and that he was there thanks to [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], leading Romanoff to inform Rogers about [[Operation Paperclip]], and how Zola was recruited into [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] after [[World War II]].
[[File:Catws 03790.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola reveals his deception to [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]]]
Informing them about Hydra's history and philosophy to prove it was him, Zola took the opportunity to reveal the details about Hydra's secret agenda all those years, its plans for [[Project Insight]], its infiltration of [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] and its long history with continuing to create chaos across the modern world. He also mentioned having written an [[Zola's Algorithm|algorithm]] to be employed by Project Insight, which would target potential threats to Hydra.
[[File:Still3.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Zola's mainframe gets destroyed by [[STRIKE]]]]
However, the entire time in fact, Zola was actually stalling both Rogers and Romanoff until [[Hydra]] could attack. Shortly thereafter, Romanoff learned of Zola's deception and they attempted to escape, only for Zola to lock them inside, awaiting several heatseekers fired by [[STRIKE]] on [[Alexander Pierce]]'s orders. Zola remarked that it was better for them and they and he were both out of time. The missiles destroyed [[Camp Lehigh]], and Zola's mainframe with it.{{Ref|CATWS}}

===Legacy===
====Project Insight's Launch====
{{Quote|The timetable has moved. [[Hydra|Our]] window is limited. [[Steve Rogers|Two]] [[Black Widow|targets]], Level Six. They already cost me Zola. I want confirmed death in ten hours.|[[Alexander Pierce]] to [[Winter Soldier]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
Having witnessed the explosion, [[Brock Rumlow]] informed [[Alexander Pierce]] about Zola's ultimate death and the survival of Rogers and Romanoff. Back on his house, Pierce told the [[Winter Soldier]] about the situation and asked him to have both Rogers and Romanoff killed in ten hours so they could [[Hydra Uprising|proceed]] with their plans as their interference had cost him Zola.{{Ref|CATWS}}

====Planning the Time Heist====
In [[2023]], Zola's work with the [[Tesseract]] was noted by the [[Avengers]] when they studied the history of the [[Infinity Stones]] in preparation for the [[Time Heist]].{{Ref|AE}}<ref name="AEVFX"/>

==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Captain America: The Winter Soldier. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|Zola's [[Zola's Algorithm|algorithm]] evaluates people's past to predict their future.|[[Jasper Sitwell]] to [[Steve Rogers]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
*'''Computer Physiology''': When Zola's organic body started dying, he created himself a computer body to live longer. His face was seen on a computer screen while what he called his "brain" were the many computer systems surrounding the screen. Zola was able to identify [[Natasha Romanoff]] by her full name as well as her birth day. He was able to do this against his long time foe, [[Steve Rogers]] as well.
**'''Longevity''': Zola uploaded his mind to a computer which meant he would live forever, unless killed by an exterior force like the missile that killed him.
**'''Computer Interaction''': [[File:Catws 03777.jpg|thumb|250px|Zola transfers to another computer]] Being a computer, Zola could easily access his brain and the many computer systems surrounding him. When [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] punched the monitor, cracking it, Zola easily put his face back up on another computer.

===Abilities===
<!-- The power list and levels has been carefully reviewed and approved with the media released as of Captain America: The Winter Soldier. DO NOT MAKE arbitrary changes to them or it may lead to blocks. If something is wrong, please contact WikiProjects: Powers & Abilities -->
{{Quote|I must congratulate you, Arnim. Your designs do not disappoint, though they may require some slight reinforcement.|[[Johann Schmidt]] to Arnim Zola|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
*'''Genius-Level Intellect''': Zola was a brilliant scientist and engineer, able to successfully invent a machine in the [[1940s]] that could absorb and harness the [[Tesseract]]'s energy, successfully replicate a version of [[Abraham Erskine]]'s [[Super Soldier Serum]], and upload his entire mind into [[1970s]] computers. As an artificial intelligence, Zola was able to decipher the pattern of human behavior and developed an [[Zola's Algorithm|algorithm]] for [[Hydra]] to deploy for [[Project Insight]].
*'''Master Scientist''': Arnim Zola was the greatest scientist amongst those who worked for the Third Reich, and later Hydra. He was interested both in technology and genetics, though he preferred making the new weapons to aid the Axis in world conquest instead of enhancing human bodies to the peak of human perfection.
{{Quote|Are you ready, Dr. Zola?"<br>"My machine requires the most delicate calibration. Forgive me if I seem overcautious.|[[Johann Schmidt]] and Arnim Zola|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
*'''Master Engineer''': Zola designed many weapons years ahead of his time. From his early experiments designing [[Hydra Exo-Skeleton|Exo-skeletons]] and [[Hydra Mini Tank|battle tanks]], to the breakthroughs he made once he was able to collect the energy of the [[Tesseract]], Zola had a natural talent for designing advanced weapons systems.
*'''Expert Spy''': Zola was able to infiltrate [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] and grow [[Hydra]] within S.H.I.E.L.D. without the smartest minds and spies in the world figuring it out. He was able to keep his cover even despite being a known Hydra ally.
*'''Bilingualism''': Zola was fluent in his native German, as well as English.

==Equipment==
===Other Equipment===
{{Quote|I am not a recording, Fräulein.<ref>Translates from German to: "''Young lady.''"</ref> I may not be the man I was when the [[Steve Rogers|Captain]] [[Capture of Arnim Zola|took me prisoner]] in [[1945]], but I am.|Arnim Zola to [[Black Widow]]|Captain America: The Winter Soldier}}
*'''Computer System''': With [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s resources, Zola was able to build an entire computer system which his mind was uploaded into as an artificially intelligent user interface. Though Zola's body died in [[1972]], his mind continued to live in cyberspace. By the [[2010s]], though now decades old, the computers were still operational.

===Vehicles===
{{Quote|Not a scratch, doctor. Not a scratch.|[[Red Skull]] to Arnim Zola|Captain America: The First Avenger}}
*'''[[Johann Schmidt's Coupe]]''': Zola used [[Johann Schmidt]]'s coupe to escape [[Hydra]]'s [[Hydra Base Camp C3|Austrian facility]] when it was getting [[Liberation of Allied Prisoners of War|destroyed]].
*'''[[Schnellzug EB912]]''': Zola rode the Schnellzug EB912 and [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]], [[Bucky Barnes]], and [[Gabe Jones]] [[Capture of Arnim Zola|infiltrating]] the train. Zola separated Barnes and Rogers and attacked them, as Barnes fell off the train. Jones found Zola and held him at gunpoint, capturing him and bringing him into Allied custody.

