==Trivia==
[[File:Arnim Zola's Plans.jpg|thumb|250px|Arnim Zola's designs for an Android Body]]
*In the comics, Arnim Zola is a geneticist whose consciousness is eventually transferred into a robotic body. His first appearance in ''[[Captain America: The First Avenger]]'' as a close-up of his face on a cathode ray tube monitor, evokes his comic-book counterpart.
*In the archived photograph Zola shows to [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and [[Black Widow]] of the [[Operation Paperclip]] rocket scientists, Zola takes the place of {{WPS|Helmut Hölzer}}. Besides an uncanny resemblance, Hölzer also worked on advanced computer/targeting systems like Zola.
*Zola is a vegetarian.{{Ref|CATFA}}
*In the recap of the third issue of ''[[Captain America: First Vengeance]]'', Arnim Zola was mistakenly referred as "Dr. Emile Zola".{{Ref|CAFV3}}

==Behind the Scenes==
*Arnim Zola in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] is the second live-action incarnation of the character, following an incarnation portrayed by Peter Haworth.
*According to [[Stephen McFeely]], the filmmakers wanted to give Arnim Zola a backstory rather than introduce him as he is in the comics where "he's a head in a TV screen in a big robot body". McFeely further elaborated that during ''[[Captain America: The First Avenger]]'', Zola serves as "the audience's eyes to all the over-the-top evil that going on in the film."{{Ref|TAoCATFA}}
*Zola's role in the story of ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' as the one who reveals Hydra's history was initially controversial as it was felt to be a "''too {{WPS|Science fiction|sci-fi}} moment''" in a film deemed as a realistic conspiracy thriller.{{Ref|CATWSAC}}
*Zola was supposed to appear in ''[[Ant-Man (film)|Ant-Man]]'', with concept art suggesting he downloaded a copy of his artificial intelligence to an android body akin to his comics appearance, but his appearance was ultimately scrapped.<ref>[http://www.cbr.com/ant-man-concept-art-reveals-arnim-zola-originally-had-a-role/ ANT-MAN CONCEPT ART REVEALS ARNIM ZOLA ORIGINALLY HAD A ROLE]</ref>

